name: AL B
review: Cafe coffee day when you get there, itÃ¢â‚¬â„¢s table service so sit down anywhere. They arenÃ¢â‚¬â„¢t quick to take your order but thatÃ¢â‚¬â„¢s because in Bangalore India itÃ¢â‚¬â„¢s a slow paced environment for food and restaurants.The selection of beverages is amazing. You can have coffee, tea, mocktails, or just water. You also have a large selection of food. From savory to sweet. There are also pairings available. If youÃ¢â‚¬â„¢re veg or non-veg an option is there for you.The food... wow! Flavor. It is not what Americans expect from India. (Most) People  stereotype Indian food as curry, masala, rice and wheat. But they have a great twist on the foods westerns and others have come to love.My meal: triple cheesy churn has burger. Veg burger with a a relish and baby potatoes roasted. Each bite was an explosion of flavor. The smoked guda complimenting the spices from the vegetable patty. The cream cheese was all the star though. It was Slightly sweet but some heat to it as well.The relish; mild in heat with bell pepper and lettuce. Mixed with the baby potatoes seasoned with love, it gives a nice starchy contrast to the rich burger.The coffee. Light. Sweet. But strong. I enjoyed  monsoon mist pour over at the recommendation of my server. The aroma from the grounds was surrounding my senses, but as soon as the water hit, the perfume of sweet coffee permeated the air. The sweetness from the coffee compliments the flavors of the veg burger very well. All of this for about 870 Rs ($14 USD) and 120 Rs tip. name: B L
review: Absolutely not worth it. I arrived and ordered a vanilla cold brew coffee and sat down to enjoy my beverage. I was informed no photos were allowed in the restaurant, which is interesting given the number of photos currently attached to the review page... But anyway, that wasn't the problem -We'll start with the washrooms. Dirty dirty dirty. Garbage overflowing outside of the bin and a broken seat cover. For a place that tries to market itself as worthy of an automatic 5% service charge, the washroom sure was a let down.But what was perhaps most disappointing was my beverage, followed by the complete LACK OF SERVICE from the staff. I took one sip and gagged. The "hint of vanilla" that was used to describe the beverage was actually a punch in the face of sugar. It was completely unpalatable. I left the full beverage and went to the cash register. Again, for the 5% service charge, not a single person came by to check on me or ask if I was enjoying the beverage. When I went to the register, I informed the staff member that I had left the entire beverage because it was far too sweet and not good at all. I was then met with the stares and gazes of about 6 other employees, at least one of whom looked like a supervisor/manager, who watched as I was then made to pay Rs. 283 for a beverage I never drank. And yes, that was with the added service charge, because for some reason, they felt like their disgusting beverage, absentee staff, and grimey washrooms deserved an extra 5%.Will not be returning and will be advising others of the same.Absolutely not worth it. name: Saurabh
review:
One of the better CafÃ© Coffee Days left after the last three years of downsizing. The structure is beautifully designed with ceiling  to floor glass facades. There's plentiful natural light streaming through most of the day. Outdoors seating though limited to three tables caters to smokers and overlooks the busy Outer Ring Road. The wifi is mostly good, encouraging work-from-home types to work over rounds of cappuccinos. The sandwiches and rolls, both vegetarian and non-vegetarian are delicious, though pricey. There's a wide range of sundaes, shakes, smoothies and cold coffees. Their signature hot coffees are as reliable as ever.Vegetarian options: Sandwiches.Kid-friendliness: No. It's primarily for older people to hang out and work, have meetings or relax with a book.Parking: Parking bikes on the side of the road shouldn't be too difficult but parking cars is an issue on the busy Outer Ring Road.Wheelchair accessibility: Yes.Dietary restrictions: Gluten-free options mostly unavailable. Vegan options limited.Food: 4/5Â Â |Â Â Service: 4/5Â Â |Â Â Atmosphere: 4/5Parking space
Somewhat difficult to find parking

name: Jacob Philips
review: One of the worst experiences EVER!The table we sat at had the previous diners left overs on it and nobody was available to clean up. I had to do it myself. The staff were nowhere to be seen! It looked like they all took a break together.When I went to order my drink the staff were all aloof and least bothered to help out with my order. He handed me a menu card and asked me to choose from that one. Being a relatively new customer I didn't know there was an ACTUAL menu (which I found out later). I chose one item and he said that the drink that I wanted was out of stock and he suggested that I take the most expensive item on that menu! I clearly told him I wanted a simple cold drink and he proceeded to get me what can only be described as a COLD ESPRESSO! I mean even with sugar in it, it was basically inedible! We complained about this but he was unwilling to change the order and said that I'd have to pay extra to "upgrade" the present one! He did hear that I wanted something cold. I would assume he knows their entire menu by heart since he works there, but he chose to exploit me. I ended up paying Rs.210 for nothing!Normally I stay away from this chain mainly because they overcharge for simple things and this was my first visit after almost 3 years. It was a serious wake up call for me as to why I stayed away in the first place!Pathetic service! review: The pandemic has hit many & I am one if them. Post the relaxation in Lock-down, this has become my office. 75% if the crowd is here for professional reasons. review: Cafe Coffee Day CCDOrdered a cafe latte today from the CCD outlet at Sigma mall, Cunningham Road.Was surprised to see that gave the beverage in a paper cup(price: 145). You can't charge 150 for just pouring coffee from the vending machine.(i can also do that).Also, when I ordered the coffee, i paid by card and the lady at the counter didnt give me any bill. She only gave the card transaction receipt.It was only when I asked for the bill(sometime later, after receiving my coffee and starting to consume it) that she generated the bill and gave me.When she generated the bill later, she realized that she charged extra (145 instead of 131) and gave me the balance amount back.It was an empty counter. I wonder how can the person at service forget to generate the bill only and charge extra from customer! name: Jevika Shetty
review: I visited the Cafe at Kormangla branch. This was an unpleasant experience for two reasons - firstly, the place can often get super crowded and noisy. This by default takes away the charm of a cafe and turns into more of a bustling restaurant. Therefore, we found it very difficult to work in there. Secondly, the staff seems to care more about making money than actually providing you a courteous service. We were a group of 6-8 people who met to discuss work, and found a spot outdoors. When the atmosphere got too noisy, we decided to move in. Except the staff denied us a spot inside on the account that each of us had to order something.After we did so, we finally moved in and continued our discussion, only to be approached by the staff once again. This time they politely "kicked us out" because they didn't want customers to take up space for "too long", else they may lose potential customers. This was my first ever experience wherein a cafe staff demands it's customers leave on such a note.Therefore, definitely not visiting this cafe again and would highly recommend other cafes in the area over this one, if you want a warmer experience. Two stars given to these guys just because of a good variety of beverages and desserts.I visited the Cafe at Kormangla branch. name: Raj Ranjan Dhir
review: You can't buy happiness, but you can buy Coffee.This Cafe Coffee Day is in top of my list of all Cafe Coffee Day Lounges because I have got some really lovely memories attached to this place. It is a nice cozy place perfect for dating or simply hanging out with friends or your loved ones. The best thing is its open till midnight. So it's quite relaxing and romantic at same time to spend time your loved ones and having a midnight dessert.The ambience is quite nice in this place. There are huge glass doors with nice sofa seats next to the glass door and then it leads to small section where their is souvenir stand with glasses and saucers. There is one hugger stand that has coffee beans and powders that been bought from CCD. The outlet has these special fancy fans fitted to the ceiling which also adds to the decor of this place.Though Coffee makes me happy, but I don't get the whole hype about the Coffee chains and the logic behind the pricing. I do enjoy a cuppa once a while but find the filter coffee more comforting and tasty. Also at a lesser than quarter the price.The place has multiple items in terms of food and drinks. This time we had ordered the Cranberry specials which was part of the Magical Brews. The Cranberry Latte was ok, tasted just like the regular Latte but the Cranberry Hot Chocolate was delicious with a strong flavour of Cranberry. The staff recommended the Cripsy Veg Wrap when asked about something fresh and it was fresh and nice. Now looking forward to trying the Red Velvet specials from the Magical Brew Series. Ordered some Almond Biscuits, they were actually the rusk that we get at bakeries that can be dipped in Coffee/ Tea and taken. The taste of the biscuits is quite good and it goes along quite well with the Coffee that we end up taking.This is a good place to come along with friends and family, have a conversation over Coffee One experience that surprised was that the person at the store was quite hesitant when I wanted to click pictures. He was telling it was against policy. It was little surprised why he did that because I have not heard of it anywhere else. I would leave it up to the CCD Management to handle.You can't buy happiness, but you can buy Coffee.This Cafe Coffee Day is in top of my list of all Cafe Coffee Day Lounges because â€¦More

name: Tarveez Ashraf
review: We had one of the worst experience in coffee day here, first of all I am not big at going to coffee days , I think they're expensive for any normal visit. But since I had a meeting today we decided to do that here and we ordered the beverage and started with the meeting.Once we finished our beverage and some time later a server or a manager approaches us and throws the menu in front of us during the meeting and says "you might need to order again".we were like WTF man?
